President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has sent a notice to Congress stating that the national emergency with respect to the situation in Mali, which was declared in Executive Order 13882 on July 26, 2019, will continue beyond July 26, 2021. The President cites various reasons for the continuation of the national emergency, including repeated violations of ceasefire arrangements, terrorist activities, drug trafficking, human rights abuses, and attacks against civilians and security forces. President Biden has determined that this situation poses an unusual and extraordinary threat to the national security and foreign policy of the United States.